{"id": "hb6dw4", "title": "Zoomers: If you are down more than you ever thought possible, and are staring into the abyss", "selftext": "Learn from HTZ, and research the costs and benefits of using bankruptcy to restructure your finances.\n\nIt doesn't matter if you are negative a million bajillion dollars, it could just get reset to zero, or down to a monthly payment you can afford. Corporations do this all the time. You know who declared bankruptcy and got back on their feet? Marvel Entertainment. Six Flags. Texaco. Sbarro. Apple nearly declared bankruptcy in 1997 before they accepted help from Microsoft. Celebrities file bankruptcy [all the time](https://www.levittslafkes.com/articles/famous-people-who-have-filed-bankruptcy/). Even Donny Pump.\n\nBankruptcy is a form of outside help written into the Constitution. It's an economic right that you should consider taking advantage of before doing something drastic.\n\nThere are downsides. If you spent money on dumb shit, you might have to give it up. You will face economic challenges others won't. It will be hard to buy a house. By the way though, you weren't going to buy a house any time soon anyway. An entire generation just spent the last 10 years being unable to buy houses even without bankruptcy on their records.  \n\nThere may be more. I have not gone through it myself. This isn't legal advice or investing advice. It's probably not as fun as trading options. But it's not like you're going to prison. \n\nIt's not like you're doing something permanent. It's not like your friends and family will spend the rest of their lives wondering what more they could have done for you.\n\nThink about the time you spent researching your trades, and think about the amount of time you should spend researching your economic options before you do something irreversible.\n\nYou have a lot of smart decisions ahead of you. Be glad, you learned an important economic lesson while you still have time to take advantage of it.", "created_utc": 1592449424.0, "permalink": "/r/wallstreetbets/comments/hb6dw4/zoomers_if_you_are_down_more_than_you_ever/", "is_self": true}